_Hif’il_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_hif’il_ future tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|                | *Singular*                           |\< | *Plural*                             |\<  |
| *First-Person* | אַבְדִּיל<br>_avdil_<br>I will separate | \< | נַבְדִּיל<br>_navdil_<br>We will separate | \< |
| *Second-Person* |תַּבְדִּיל <br>_tavdil_<br> You [male] will separate | תַּבְדִּילִי <br>_tavdili_<br> You [female] will separate  | תַּבְדִּילוּ <br>_tavdilu_<br> You [males] will separate  | תַּבְדֵּלְנָה <br>_tavdeilnau_<br> You [females] will separate  |
| *Third-Person* |יַבְדִּיל <br>_yavdil_<br> He will separate | תַּבְדִּיל <br>_tavdil_<br> She will separate  | יַבְדִּילוּ <br>_yavdilu_<br> [Those males] will separate  | תַּבְדֵּלְנָה <br>_tavdeilnau_<br> [Those females] will separate  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ב, ‎ד, and ל above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
